[3] Texas (Dallas County): locally acquired
Date: Fri 14 Feb 2014
Source: The Dallas Morning news [edited]
http://www.dallasnews.com/news/metro/20140214-dallas-county-confirms-rare-case-of-adult-measles-not-linked-to-travel.ece


A Dallas County resident has been confirmed with a rare case of adult measles, the county health department said Fri 14 Feb 2014. The infected person is recovering after hospitalization, said a statement from the county. The source of infection is unknown because the case did not involve recent international travel, and there is no known link to 2 pediatric measles cases reported by Collin County in January 2014.

A measles outbreak in the summer of 2013 in Tarrant and Denton counties placed the state on high alert for the infectious virus. All 20 measles cases were traced to a church in northwest Tarrant County, health officials said. The initial measles case in that outbreak involved an adult church member who had traveled to a part of the world where measles infections are common.

2 measles cases reported in Dallas County in 2014 were linked to foreign travel but did not spread.

[Byline: Sherry Jacobson]

